# Tool onboarding phases

Parameter tools use three phases. **Never** jump straight from the first slider touch to a full animation or chart.

## 1. Intro (optional)

Explore tools with no required inputs use `<IntroState>` — the learner picks a path or presses Start before anything loads.

## 2. Build (`GuidedInputFlow`)

Slider / input tools use `<GuidedInputFlow>` step-by-step:

- One active step at a time; completed steps stay editable.
- The right panel stays a **placeholder** while building — no pies, plots, or simulations yet.
- `useTouchedFields` marks a step complete when the learner **engages** that control (sliders always have a value; "touched" ≠ "confirmed").

## 3. Visualization (explicit confirm)

When every step is complete, **do not** render the visualization automatically.

Use `useVisualizationGate()`:

```tsx
const gate = useVisualizationGate();
const buildComplete = /* all steps touched or filled */;
const showVisualization = buildComplete && gate.visualizationConfirmed;

{!showVisualization ? (
  <GuidedInputFlow
    awaitingVisualizationConfirm={buildComplete && !gate.visualizationConfirmed}
    onVisualizationConfirm={gate.confirmVisualization}
    onReset={() => { /* reset values */ gate.resetVisualization(); fields.reset(); }}
    …
  />
) : (
  /* full visualization */
)}
```

`onFillExample` may pre-fill values and touch fields, but it must **not** call `confirmVisualization` — the learner still presses **Show visualization**.

## Sliders during build

Sliders belong **above** expanding output (see `slider-ux.mdc`). During the build phase there is no heavy output beside the placeholder / confirm panel.
